## 3. Psychological Principles Exploited

Social engineers exploit fundamental human psychological tendencies:

### Authority
People comply with requests from perceived authority figures.
- Attacker impersonates boss, IT department, bank, government
- Victim feels obligated to comply without questioning

### Urgency and Scarcity
Creating time pressure prevents careful thinking.
- "Your account will be closed in 24 hours"
- "Act now or lose your money"
- "Limited time offer"

### Social Proof
People follow what others appear to be doing.
- "Everyone in your company has already updated their details"
- "Other customers have already verified their accounts"

### Liking and Familiarity
People comply more readily with people they like or know.
- Attacker researches victim on social media to establish rapport
- Uses names of mutual connections to build trust

### Fear
Fear of loss, punishment, or negative consequences drives hasty action.
- "Your account has been compromised"
- "You owe unpaid taxes — pay immediately to avoid legal action"
- "Suspicious activity detected on your account"

### Reciprocity
People feel obligated to return favours.
- Attacker provides small genuine help before making request
- Victim feels social obligation to comply

